law.text:
// EFFECTIVE UNTIL JUNE 30, 2015 PER CHAPTERS 280 AND 281 OF 2011 //
The following persons when engaged in the regular course of their respective businesses and professions:
An attorney at law who is admitted to the Maryland Bar while the attorney at law is providing professional legal services in an attorney-client relationship;
An escrow agent;
A certified public accountant;
A banking institution, other-state bank, national banking association, credit union, or savings and loan association;
A person that:
Provides a bill payer service, as defined in § 12-401 of this title;
Does not initiate any contract with individual creditors of a debtor to compromise a debt or arrange a new payment schedule; and
Does not provide any debt counseling services;
A person that provides an accelerated mortgage payment service, as defined in § 12-401 of this title;
A title insurer, title insurance agency, or abstract company; or
A judicial officer or a person acting under a court order;
A person while performing services incidental to the dissolution, winding up, or liquidation of a partnership, corporation, or other business enterprise;
A trade or mercantile association acting in the course of arranging the adjustment of debts with a business establishment;
A mortgage lender, as defined in § 11-501 of this article:
That is licensed by the Commissioner; and
While engaged in the mortgage lending business, as defined in § 11-501 of this article; or
An employee of a mortgage lender; or
A collection agency, as defined in § 7-101 of the Business Regulation Article:
That is licensed by the State Collection Agency Licensing Board; and
While engaged in the collection agency business, as defined in § 7-101 of the Business Regulation Article.
